From: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Wed, 24 Nov 2021 22:40:25 +0100
Subject: RDMA/cxgb4: Use bitmap_set() when applicable
Patch-mainline: v5.17-rc1
Git-commit: 967a578af0c6d0c6c50ee5f9c48216cd2eebe4ef
References: jsc#PED-1508

The 'alloc->table' bitmap has just been allocated, so this is safe to use
the faster and non-atomic 'bitmap_set()' function. There is no need to
hand-write it.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/fd978b837935ed04863ffecfd495c4601a986df6.1637789139.git.christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr
Signed-off-by: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Signed-off-by: Jason Gunthorpe <jgg@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/infiniband/hw/cxgb4/id_table.c |    5 +----
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/infiniband/hw/cxgb4/id_table.c
+++ b/drivers/infiniband/hw/cxgb4/id_table.c
@@ -82,8 +82,6 @@ void c4iw_id_free(struct c4iw_id_table *
 int c4iw_id_table_alloc(struct c4iw_id_table *alloc, u32 start, u32 num,
 			u32 reserved, u32 flags)
 {
-	int i;
-
 	alloc->start = start;
 	alloc->flags = flags;
 	if (flags & C4IW_ID_TABLE_F_RANDOM)
@@ -97,8 +95,7 @@ int c4iw_id_table_alloc(struct c4iw_id_t
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
 	if (!(alloc->flags & C4IW_ID_TABLE_F_EMPTY))
-		for (i = 0; i < reserved; ++i)
-			set_bit(i, alloc->table);
+		bitmap_set(alloc->table, 0, reserved);
 
 	return 0;
 }
